This paper deals with the design and analysis of codes for multiple-access collision channels, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT). The paper also involves combinatorial structures such as codes and their properties, which falls under the category of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) and discrete mathematics (cs.DC). The paper may also be relevant to networked systems (cs.NI) and signal processing (cs.SI) due to its application in communication systems.
